  "text": "The high prevalences of HR-HPV and multiple infections found in this study (83.4% and 60.5%, respectively) are consistent with previous reports from studies conducted in Canada, the United States, and Europe [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The most common type found in our study, HPV-16, is also the most common in all ; age at first sexual intercourse, 17 years; condom use during anal intercourse in past 12 months, occasionally; smoking history, never; geographic origin, Europe; and education level, university). Shaded regions are 95% confidence intervals.",
